VALUES
(43, 21, 15, 23, 40, 11, 11, 'Feed my lambs', 'Shepherding and Feeding Imagery', 'This connection highlights the theme of shepherding and care for the flock. Both passages emphasize the act of feeding and nurturing lambs, illustrating a shared responsibility for guiding and supporting the vulnerable.', 'theme', 0.43299999999999994, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 21, 15, 62, 4, 19, 19, 'lovest thou me more than these', 'Love and Response Connection', 'Both passages emphasize the theme of love, with John 21:15 highlighting Peter''s love for Jesus and 1 John 4:19 stating that our love for Him is a response to His prior love for us. This connection highlights the reciprocal nature of love in the relationship between Jesus and His followers.', 'theme', 0.43299999999999994, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 21, 15, 45, 15, 1, 1, 'Feed my lambs', 'Love and Responsibility', 'This connection highlights the theme of caring for others. In John 21:15, Jesus instructs Peter to ''Feed my lambs,'' emphasizing the responsibility to nurture. Similarly, Romans 15:1 calls for the strong to bear the infirmities of the weak, reinforcing the idea of supporting others.', 'theme', 0.426, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 21, 15, 47, 5, 14, 15, 'lovest thou me more than these', 'Love and Service Connection', 'This connection highlights the theme of love motivating action. In John 21:15, Jesus asks Peter about his love, linking it to the responsibility to ''Feed my lambs.'' Similarly, 2 Corinthians 5:14-15 emphasizes that the love of Christ compels believers to live for Him, not themselves.', 'theme', 0.398, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 21, 15, 60, 1, 8, 8, 'lovest thou me', 'Love and Belief Connection', 'Both passages emphasize the theme of love for Jesus. In John 21:15, Peter expresses his love for Christ, while 1 Peter 1:8 speaks of loving Jesus without having seen him. This connection highlights the continuity of love and faith in the believer''s relationship with Christ.', 'theme', 0.384, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 21, 15, 60, 5, 1, 4, 'Feed my lambs', 'Feeding the Flock Connection', 'This connection highlights the theme of shepherding and care for God''s people. Both passages emphasize the responsibility to ''feed'' and guide the flock, linking Peter''s commission from Jesus to his later exhortation to elders.', 'theme', 0.384, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 21, 15, 49, 6, 24, 24, 'lovest thou me', 'Love for Christ Connection', 'This connection highlights the theme of loving Jesus. In John 21:15, Peter is asked about his love for Christ, while Ephesians 6:24 emphasizes loving the Lord Jesus Christ in sincerity.', 'theme', 0.377, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 21, 16, 44, 20, 28, 28, 'Feed my sheep', 'Feeding the Flock Connection', 'Both passages emphasize the responsibility to ''feed'' the community of believers. In John, Jesus instructs Peter to ''Feed my sheep,'' while in Acts, leaders are urged to ''feed the church of God.''', 'theme', 0.398, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 21, 16, 60, 5, 2, 2, 'Feed my sheep', 'Feeding the Flock Connection', 'This connection highlights the theme of pastoral care in both passages. In John 21:16, Jesus commands Peter to ''Feed my sheep,'' while 1 Peter 5:2 instructs leaders to ''Feed the flock of God,'' emphasizing the responsibility of nurturing believers.', 'theme', 0.377, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 21, 16, 60, 2, 25, 25, 'Feed my sheep', 'Shepherd and Sheep Connection', 'This connection highlights the theme of shepherding and care for sheep. In John 21:16, Jesus instructs Peter to ''Feed my sheep,'' while 1 Peter 2:25 refers to Christ as the ''Shepherd'' of souls, emphasizing the role of guidance and protection.', 'theme', 0.349, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 21, 16, 19, 100, 3, 3, 'Feed my sheep', 'Connection of Sheep Imagery', 'Both passages emphasize the concept of sheep, with John 21:16 referencing the act of feeding Jesus'' sheep and Psalms 100:3 identifying the people as the sheep of God''s pasture. This connection highlights the pastoral care and responsibility inherent in the relationship between God and His followers.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 21, 16, 43, 10, 11, 16, 'Feed my sheep', 'Shepherd and Sheep Connection', 'Both passages emphasize the relationship between the shepherd and the sheep. In John 21:16, Jesus instructs Peter to ''Feed my sheep,'' linking to His role as the good shepherd in John 10:11-16, where He lays down His life for them.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 21, 16, 19, 95, 7, 7, 'Feed my sheep', 'Sheep and Care for Them', 'This connection highlights the theme of shepherding and care for God''s people. In John 21:16, Jesus instructs Peter to ''Feed my sheep,'' paralleling Psalms 95:7, which refers to the people as ''the sheep of his hand.''', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 21, 16, 38, 13, 7, 7, 'Feed my sheep', 'Connection of Shepherd and Sheep', 'This connection highlights the role of the shepherd in both passages. In John, Jesus instructs Peter to ''Feed my sheep,'' while Zechariah speaks of a shepherd being smitten, leading to the scattering of the sheep.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 21, 17, 43, 13, 38, 38, NULL, 'Peter''s Denial and Restoration', 'Both passages emphasize Peter''s threefold denial and subsequent affirmation of love for Jesus. The repetition in both contexts highlights Peter''s journey from failure to restoration.', 'theme', 0.398, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 21, 17, 41, 14, 72, 72, 'Lovest thou me?', 'Peter''s Denial and Restoration', 'This connection highlights Peter''s journey from denial to affirmation of love. In Mark, Peter''s denial is marked by the crowing of the cock, while in John, he is asked three times if he loves Jesus, paralleling his three denials.', 'theme', 0.37, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 21, 17, 43, 16, 30, 30, 'thou knowest all things', 'Knowledge of All Things', 'Both passages emphasize the theme of knowledge, specifically that Jesus possesses complete understanding. In John 21:17, Peter acknowledges Jesus'' omniscience with ''thou knowest all things,'' which parallels the disciples'' affirmation in John 16:30 of Jesus'' divine knowledge.', 'theme', 0.37, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 21, 17, 49, 4, 30, 30, 'grieved', 'Connection of Grief and Love', 'This connection highlights the theme of grief in both passages. In John, Peter is grieved by Jesus'' questioning of his love, while in Ephesians, believers are instructed not to grieve the Holy Spirit.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 21, 17, 66, 2, 23, 23, 'Lovest thou me', 'Connection of Love and Works', 'This connection highlights the theme of accountability in love and actions. In John, Peter''s love for Jesus leads to a call to care for others, while Revelation emphasizes that individuals will be judged according to their works, reflecting their true commitment.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'medium', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 21, 17, 44, 1, 24, 24, 'thou knowest all things', 'Knowledge of Hearts Connection', 'This connection highlights the theme of divine knowledge, as both passages emphasize the Lord''s understanding of human hearts and intentions. In John 21:17, Jesus acknowledges His knowledge of Peter''s love, while Acts 1:24 refers to the Lord''s knowledge of the hearts of men.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 21, 17, 44, 15, 8, 8, 'thou knowest all things', 'Connection of Divine Knowledge', 'This connection highlights the theme of divine knowledge, as both passages emphasize God''s understanding of human hearts and intentions. In John 21:17, Jesus acknowledges Peter''s love, while Acts 15:8 states that God knows the hearts of people.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 21, 18, 43, 13, 36, 36, NULL, 'Peter''s Future Following', 'Both passages emphasize Peter''s future following of Jesus. In John 21:18, the reference to being girded and carried suggests a transition in Peter''s life, paralleling the idea in John 13:36 that he cannot follow Jesus now but will do so later.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 21, 18, 44, 12, 3, 4, 'another shall gird thee', 'Peter''s Imprisonment and Future', 'This connection highlights Peter''s future suffering and captivity. In John 21:18, the phrase ''another shall gird thee'' suggests a loss of freedom, paralleling Peter''s imprisonment in Acts 12:3-4.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 21, 18, 44, 21, 11, 11, 'girdedst thyself, and walkedst whither thou wouldest', 'Binding and Submission Theme', 'This connection highlights the theme of being bound and led by others. In John 21:18, the imagery of being girded and carried suggests a loss of autonomy, which parallels the binding of Paul in Acts 21:11.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 21, 18, 43, 12, 27, 28, 'stretch forth thy hands', 'Connection of Suffering and Glory', 'This connection highlights the theme of suffering leading to glorification. In John 21:18, the reference to being carried where one would not go parallels the troubled soul in John 12:27, indicating a journey towards a greater purpose.', 'theme', 0.293, 'medium', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 21, 18, 47, 5, 4, 4, NULL, 'Connection of Mortality and Life', 'This connection highlights the theme of transformation from mortality to life. In John 21:18, the imagery of being girded and carried suggests a transition, paralleling 2 Corinthians 5:4''s focus on being clothed upon, emphasizing the movement from a state of burden to one of life.', 'theme', 0.286, 'medium', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 21, 19, 61, 1, 14, 14, 'Follow me', 'Connection of Death and Following', 'This connection highlights the theme of death and following Christ. In John 21:19, Jesus indicates Peter''s future death, while 2 Peter 1:14 reflects Peter''s awareness of his impending death, linking both passages through the concept of following Jesus even unto death.', 'theme', 0.356, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 21, 19, 43, 21, 22, 22, 'Follow me', 'Call to Follow Jesus', 'Both passages emphasize the command to ''Follow me,'' highlighting the importance of discipleship. The context of each verse underscores the personal nature of following Jesus, regardless of others'' paths.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 21, 19, 40, 10, 38, 38, 'Follow me', 'Following Christ''s Call', 'This connection highlights the theme of following Jesus despite the cost. Both passages emphasize the necessity of taking up one''s cross and following Him, indicating a commitment to discipleship that may involve suffering or sacrifice.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 21, 19, 50, 1, 20, 20, 'by what death he should glorify God', 'Connection of Death and Glory', 'This connection highlights the theme of glorifying God through death. Both passages emphasize the idea of Christ being magnified, whether in life or death.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini')
